<br>
I do not know how I feel right now about men and women and children being hurt and killed in this.  I am at odds with myself over the fact that women will be giving birth to children who will never hear their fathers voices.  To children who, right now, are wondering when mommy and daddy are coming home, and not realizing that they are home, but in a coffin.  I cry at times thinking about this.  But, I can't stop this war.  I didn't start this war.  I can support the troops of the country I'm in (The USA), and pray that they have a safe return...knowing that many won't.  And it breaks my heart.  <br>
<br>
Until yesterday, I supported the troops, but wasn't fully behind the reasoning of the war that we started.  Until the news came up with the information that white powder substance had been found, along with hundreds of vials of anitdote.  Whether that white powder will be found to be a biological terrorism drug that was going to be used on people or not....I think now, we've started this.  We need to finish it.  Many will lose their lives, and there is never an excuse for that.  But, what if, in the end, we end up saving hundreds of thousands.  Is it worth it?  I can't, and won't answer that.  But somewhere, somehow, I would hope it all balances out.<br>
<br>
Whether people support the war or not is their choice, but I do feel you should support the troops...many who signed up did so for college money, or as a career learning choice....not to necessarily fight in a war.<br>
