I had a hard enough time watching the anonymous faces of the lost and their families...but when I saw someone that I actually knew, well, the reality hit home.  My heart breaks for all of the lost, both the Americans and the people of Iraq.  I don't claim to understand this world or war, but I know that we must band together to help mend the wounds that are being caused by it.  I hope we achieve whatever is needed to end this soon,  I hope that in the end that our reasons were valid, and that this war will liberate the people of Iraq.  Like I said, I dont' know if our reasons are valid, I don't believe anyone but the people in the government know....but I hope, and I support our troops and my country.  Call me naive if you wish, I won't be offended, it's true... <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.collectivefury.com/images/Wheatland Sig3.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
