<br>
In polite society it was customary not to speak of religion or politics at the dinner table to avoid offence.  As someone who has strong political views I always thought that was a weak position, one that ignored the importance of both of these subjects, and the need to debate.<br>
<br>
But it now makes a lot of sense.  We are a community. But the thing that we have in common is a game called Everquest, and for some we have a love of roleplaying.  <br>
<br>
Lets not pretend that we have much else in common.  We dont have a shared history, or shared culture. <br>
 <br>
There is a very simple and basic example.  The USA named the terrorist attack 9/11, it made sense to them.  But to most of the world that means 9th November.  We cant even agree how dates should work.  Lets not try and discuss complex political and philosophical issues.  <br>
<br>
Our first poster said that that these people were fighting for our freedom - we might not all agree with that view of what this war is about.  I shall not say why I think we went to war.<br>
<br>
We might all agree with the first posters first sentiment. Let us pray that no one else dies.  Lets hope there are no more deaths of Americans, my fellow Brits or Iraqis.<br>
<br>
Tanarii 40 Necro<br>
Cerris 30 SK<br>
Haldus 44 Cleric <br>
Hanil 34 Druid<br>
